nealeu:
For nicer usage, Offline.js would benefit from refactoring to ES6 module style (that'd be a lovely pull request :)
I found this article relating to using Offline.js: http://zen-and-art-of-programming.blogspot.co.uk/2014_04_01_archive.html, which uses offline via a shim.
You can also set it up via the init methods of the shim as below.
Note: I'm disabling anything AJAX related as I want my application working without meddling of AJAX requests, but also, I'm still finding some issues in getting things going reliably.
This will get the indicator working, although I'm finding... not on every page load.  I suspect there's a timing issue I need to track down.
requirejs.config({
        baseUrl: "your/base/",
        paths: {
            "offline-js": "lib/offline.min",
        },    
        shim: {
            "offline-js" : {
                exports: "Offline",
                init: function() {
                    Offline.options = {
                        interceptRequests: false,
                        requests: false
                    };
                }
            },
            "app/NetworkStuff": ["offline-js"], // example module for when you want offline-js loaded
        }
    }
